Services

Services

Private Training Sessions

Does your dog have a specific issue that you need help with? Does your dog need to learn some new skills?

This service offers in person 1-1 training sessions with a personalised training and behavior plan and ongoing support. 

 

More Info

Reactive Dog Sitting

Do you need the extra security of an experienced dog handler to care for and walk your dog for an extended amount of time?

This service offers overnight dog sitting in your home for your reactive, nervous or aggressive dog, as well as any walks that they require.

More Info

Group Classes

Do you have a new dog who needs to learn the basics? Do you want to top up your training skills?

This service offers group classes for puppies and adult dogs. It focuses on more general training and behavior, with a strong focus on having a happy, calm and engaged dog.

More Info

Training With Medical Issues

When Dogs have health issues, training requires a lot more patience and compassion to help our pets find comfort and happiness.
 

I have worked with multiple dogs, with a range of medical issues, including chronic pain, severe allergies, skin conditions and physical disabilities.

I am passionate about giving dogs a way to communicate their needs. Dogs have good days and bad days, just like us, and our expectations and training has to reflect that to get the happiest dog and owner that we can.

Neuro-Diverse Owners

As a neuro-divergent person myself, I know how important a flexible teacher is. I also know how important it is to work with fluctuating energy levels.


 

Planning for difficult days is important for Neuro-Diverse dog owners, and so is including the necessary dog training.

 

My training is there to help your dog learn how to be calm on low energy days, or resilient training methods that take difficult days into account. Consistency is important, but so is learning to live together as a balanced and happy multi-species house hold!
